applicationDomains.name: AcmeRetail - Store Operations
applicationDomains.description: acme-retail's **Store Operations** functions center around how we can best service our customer, whether they are ordering products in-person or online.

applicationDomains.name: AcmeRetail - Human Relationships
applicationDomains.description:
At acme-retail, **Human relationships (HR)** are functions that help acme-retail better serve our associates and customers. That includes recruiting, vetting, selecting, hiring, onboarding, training, promoting, paying, and firing employees and independent contractors.  And making sure that our customers have the best possible experience.


> Many of the functions of the HR department are accomplished by SaaS components like [Workday](https://https://www.workday.com/)

applicationDomains.name: AcmeRetail - Enterprise Governance
applicationDomains.description:
The **event governance** domain shapes and changes the environment (or rules of the game) for applications in other domains to achieve enterprise-wide outcomes, like joint interoperability. This is often achieved through enterprise-wide event definitions.

> Unlike other domains, no applications are hosted in the eeg domain, nor is there a domain-specific topic structure.  For more information on why, see the Solace Blog: [When to Use Centralized Event Governance](https://solace.com/blogs)

applicationVersions.description:
Mobile application used by personnel in stores for fulfillment of orders (mobile, website or partner) and for restocking shelves.


---> Added Consumer Subscription

acme-retail's innovative mobile application lets customers purchase any product available in our stores online, and have it either shipped, delivered via service like Shipt, or have it ready for pickup at any of our brick and mortar stores.  Customers get real-time updates on their orders via the app as wel.

Customers get real-time updates on their orders via the app as wel.

**Event-Driven Data Product **

This application receives all orders for the stores and produces a summarized file of the days sales complete with colorful graphs, which due to its size is placed on a shared drive for executive consumption.

The Smart Shelf is installed in selected markets and continually updates information on what products are being removed from shelves, in an effort to analyze customer trends, as well as forecast fraud.

**Emits:** Product events with Removed verb when items removed from shelf
**Consumes**: Product events with Restocked/Returned verbs when item returned to shelf

The Smart Shelf is installed in selected markets and continually updates information on what products are being removed from shelves, in an effort to analyze customer trends, as well as forecast fraud.

**Emits:** Product events with Removed verb when items removed from shelf
**Consumes**: Product events with Restocked/Returned verbs when item returned to shelf

schemaVersions.content:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<xs:schema xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" elementFormDefault="qualified">
  <xs:include schemaLocation="contact.xsd"/>
  <xs:element name="customer">
    <xs:complexType>
      <xs:all>
        <xs:element name="type" minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="1">
          <xs:simpleType>
            <xs:restriction base="xs:string">
              <xs:enumeration value="org"/>
              <xs:enumeration value="ind"/>
            </xs:restriction>
          </xs:simpleType>
        </xs:element>
        <xs:element ref="name" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
        <xs:element ref="enabled" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
        <xs:element name="customerRefId" minOccurs="0" type="xs:string" maxOccurs="1"/>
	<xs:element ref="description" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
        <xs:element ref="crmId" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
        <xs:element ref="refId" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
        <xs:element ref="phone" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
        <xs:element ref="fax" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
        <xs:element ref="vendorId" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
        <xs:element ref="addresses" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
        <xs:element ref="defaultContact" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
      </xs:all>
    </xs:complexType>
  </xs:element>
  <xs:element name="name">
    <xs:simpleType>
      <xs:restriction base="xs:string">
        <xs:minLength value="1"/>
      </xs:restriction>
    </xs:simpleType>
  </xs:element>
  <xs:element name="description" type="xs:string"/>
  <xs:element name="rankingId" type="xs:string"/>
  <xs:element name="crmId" type="xs:string"/>
  <xs:element name="refId" type="xs:string"/>
  <xs:element name="phone" type="xs:string"/>
  <xs:element name="fax" type="xs:string"/>
  <xs:element name="vendorId">
    <xs:simpleType>
      <xs:restriction base="xs:string"> 
        <xs:pattern value="([1-9][0-9]*)*"></xs:pattern>
      </xs:restriction>
    </xs:simpleType>
  </xs:element>
  <xs:element name="addresses">
    <xs:complexType>
      <xs:sequence>
        <xs:element ref="shippingSameAsBilling" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
        <xs:element ref="address" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="2"/>
      </xs:sequence>
    </xs:complexType>
  </xs:element>
  <xs:element name="shippingSameAsBilling" type="xs:boolean"/>
  <xs:element name="address">
    <xs:complexType>
      <xs:all>
        <xs:element name="type" minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="1">
          <xs:simpleType>
            <xs:restriction base="xs:string">
              <xs:enumeration value="shipping"/>
              <xs:enumeration value="billing"/>
            </xs:restriction>
          </xs:simpleType>
        </xs:element>
        <xs:element ref="street" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
        <xs:element ref="city" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
        <xs:element ref="state" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
        <xs:element ref="country" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
        <xs:element ref="zip" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
      </xs:all>
    </xs:complexType>
  </xs:element>
  <xs:element name="street" type="xs:string"/>
  <xs:element name="city" type="xs:string"/>
  <xs:element name="state" type="xs:string"/>
  <xs:element name="country" type="xs:string"/>
  <xs:element name="zip" type="xs:string"/>
  <xs:element name="defaultContact">
    <xs:complexType>
      <xs:all>
        <xs:element ref="emailId" minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="1"/>
        <xs:element ref="firstName" minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="1"/>
        <xs:element ref="lastName" minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="1"/>
        <xs:element ref="middleName" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
        <xs:element ref="locale" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>
      </xs:all>
    </xs:complexType>
  </xs:element>
</xs:schema>
